    • Method Detail

      • getStatusString

        public static java.lang.String getStatusString(int statuscode)
        Return the String human-readable representation of a valid statuscode constant. Ex: if the provided status code is 4, the routine returns "SCRIPT_NOT_EXECUTED".
        Parameters:
        statuscode - to convert to readable string.
        Returns:
        readable status string, or null if the statuscode was not known.
